      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "The Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes (RANS) k-ω SST turbulence model was selected based on published literature demonstrating its suitability for rotating machinery hemolysis prediction. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the standard for CFD hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. Model form assumptions (Newtonian blood analog, steady-state rotor-stator interface) are documented and justified for the CPB operating regime. Model form uncertainty is acknowledged and bounded within the validation evidence.",
